# Analytics Dashboard

**Route:** `dashboard` · **Arch phase:** 3 · See `ARCHITECTURE.md` §6

## Purpose

Monitor loyalty KPIs: customer engagement, point performance, transaction impact, channel performance, and campaigns. Prototype uses seeded `PointTransaction[]` + client-side `aggregations.ts`; production KPI definitions in ARCHITECTURE.md §6.1.

**Visual design:** Uses the existing portal design system (brand/slate Tailwind tokens), not the ledger theme from the greenfield PRD.

## Key UI

**Header:** "Loyalty Analytics" + Role switcher (Employee / Approver / Admin) + Export menu (PDF/PNG).

**Filters:** Start/end date, channel, source system, transaction type (hidden unless source = Saving). All filters apply globally.

**KPI groups:** Customer Engagement, Point Performance, Cost (TBD placeholder), Transaction Impact, Channel Performance, Campaign — each defined card shows value, detail, sparkline (or TBD dashed placeholder).

**Charts:** Daily/weekly/monthly trend (line + granularity toggle), MoM/YoY growth, channel performance panel (bar + reward donut), campaign performance panel, before/after campaign (14-day default window stepper).

**Other:** Client-side export (html2canvas + jsPDF), reconciliation panel (mock run, role-gated), no real-time polling.

## User flow

1. Default route on load
2. Review KPIs and charts (all driven by `aggregations.ts`)
3. Adjust filters — every KPI and chart recomputes from filtered transactions
4. If source ≠ Saving, transaction type resets to "all" and field hides
5. Toggle trend granularity; select campaign and adjust before/after window
6. Approver/Admin: run mock reconciliation and review run log
7. Export current dashboard view as PDF or PNG

## State & data

- `filters: DashboardFilters` in `DashboardPage`
- `role: DashboardRole` — reconciliation gating only (independent of rule-module role)
- `mockTransactions`, `mockCampaigns` from `src/data/dashboardMockGenerator.ts` (via `mockData.ts`)
- KPI logic in `src/data/aggregations.ts` — swap point for API later

